# Tailwind CSS Rules

## Design System

### Color Palette
Use CSS custom properties defined in `globals.css`:

```css
/* Service Categories */
--fire-*        /* Brandskydd - red tones */
--medical-*     /* Sjukvård - blue tones */
--aed-*         /* Hjärtstartare - orange tones */
--first-aid-*   /* Första hjälpen - green tones */

/* Semantic */
--text-primary, --text-secondary, --text-tertiary
--bg-primary, --bg-secondary, --bg-tertiary
--surface-primary, --surface-hover, --surface-active
```

### Typography
- Headings: `font-heading` (Sora)
- Body text: `font-body` (Inter)
- Use utility classes for sizes: `text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg`, `text-xl`

## Styling Approach

### Use Tailwind Only
```tsx
// ✅ Good - Tailwind classes
<div className="flex items-center gap-4 p-6 rounded-lg bg-white shadow">

// ❌ Bad - inline styles
<div style={{ display: 'flex', padding: '24px' }}>

// ❌ Bad - CSS modules (avoid)
<div className={styles.container}>
```

### Class Organization
Order classes logically:
1. Layout (flex, grid, position)
2. Spacing (p, m, gap)
3. Sizing (w, h, max-w)
4. Typography (text, font)
5. Colors (bg, text color, border color)
6. Effects (shadow, opacity)
7. States (hover, focus, active)
8. Responsive (sm:, md:, lg:)

```tsx
<button className="
  flex items-center justify-center
  px-4 py-2 gap-2
  w-full max-w-md
  text-sm font-medium
  bg-primary text-white border border-primary
  shadow-sm
  hover:bg-primary/90 focus:ring-2
  sm:w-auto
">
```

### Use cn() Utility
```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

interface ButtonProps {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary';
  className?: string;
}

export function Button({ variant = 'primary', className }: ButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        'px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors',
        variant === 'primary' && 'bg-primary text-white hover:bg-primary/90',
        variant === 'secondary' && 'bg-secondary text-primary hover:bg-secondary/80',
        className
      )}
    />
  );
}
```

## Responsive Design

### Mobile First
```tsx
// ✅ Good - mobile first
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row">
<div className="p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8">
<div className="text-base md:text-lg lg:text-xl">

// ❌ Bad - desktop first
<div className="flex-row md:flex-col">
```

### Breakpoints
- `sm:` - 640px (small tablets)
- `md:` - 768px (tablets)
- `lg:` - 1024px (laptops)
- `xl:` - 1280px (desktops)
- `2xl:` - 1536px (large desktops)

### Container
```tsx
<div className="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
```

