## Accessibility

### Focus States
- Always include focus styles
- Use `focus-visible` for keyboard-only focus
- Ensure sufficient contrast

```tsx
<button className="
  focus:outline-none 
  focus-visible:ring-2 
  focus-visible:ring-border-focus 
  focus-visible:ring-offset-2
">
```

### Motion
- Respect reduced motion preferences
- Use `motion-safe:` for animations

```tsx
<div className="transition-transform motion-safe:hover:scale-105">
```

## Dark Mode

### Use CSS Variables
Dark mode colors are handled via CSS custom properties:
- Light mode: Default values
- Dark mode: `[data-theme="dark"]` or `.dark` class

No need for `dark:` prefix when using CSS variables:
```tsx
// ✅ Variables auto-switch
<div className="bg-bg-primary text-text-primary">

// Only use dark: for hardcoded colors
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
```
